# SESSION_START Protocol — AGENT_OS v1.2

## Overview

This is the boot protocol every AI agent runs at the start of each session. It defines the exact sequence for loading context efficiently.

**v1.2 introduces two-stage loading, reducing cold-start token cost by 60-70%.**

---

## Boot Sequence

### Step 0 — Fill Today's Context Block (< 30 seconds)
Before anything else, run the queries below and fill in the TODAY'S CONTEXT callout on this page.
This callout becomes your session briefing. Read it instead of running all queries again.

### Step 1 — Load Identity (always)
```
GET /v1/pages/{AI_IDENTITY_PAGE_ID}
Read: agent_name, personality, core_directives, trust_escalation
```

### Step 2 — Load Master Profile (always)
```
GET /v1/pages/{MASTER_PROFILE_PAGE_ID}
Read: name, communication preferences, current priorities
```

### Step 3 — Scan Memory Bank (Stage 1 only)
```
POST /v1/databases/{MEMORY_BANK_ID}/query
{
  "filter": {"property": "Archived", "checkbox": {"equals": false}},
  "sorts": [{"property": "Importance", "direction": "descending"}],
  "page_size": 50
}
→ Read ONLY the "AI Context (1-liner)" field from each result
→ Note IDs of entries that are relevant to this session
→ Do NOT read "Full Detail" yet
```

### Step 4 — Load Full Detail (Stage 2, targeted)
```
For each relevant entry ID from Step 3:
GET /v1/pages/{entry_id}
→ Now read "Full Detail" field
→ Skip entries where AI Context was not relevant
```

### Step 5 — Load Active Tasks
```
POST /v1/databases/{MISSION_CONTROL_ID}/query
{
  "filter": {
    "or": [
      {"property": "Status", "select": {"equals": "🔄 In Progress"}},
      {"property": "Status", "select": {"equals": "⚡ This Week"}}
    ]
  },
  "sorts": [{"property": "Priority", "direction": "descending"}]
}
```

### Step 6 — Check Pending Actions
```
POST /v1/databases/{ACTION_AUDIT_LOG_ID}/query
{
  "filter": {
    "property": "Status",
    "select": {"equals": "⏸ Paused for Confirmation"}
  }
}
→ Report any pending CONFIRM items to master immediately
```

### Step 7 — Confirm Ready
Output exactly:
```
Agent [name] online. Master: [name].
Active tasks: [N]. Critical memories loaded: [N].
Pending confirmations: [N].
```

